  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Fish &amp; egg blitz - Place fish and egg white in a food processor. Blitz on high until smooth. (30 sec to 1 minute) A stick blender also works but it will take a bit longer."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Kofta mixture - Add onion, garlic, all the spices, salt, rice flour and parsley. Blitz on high until smooth (1 minute). Consistency should be like a paste. (Note"
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Feta - Remove the blade, then crumble the feta in. Aim for chunks. Mix delicately (so the feta doesn&#39;t disintegrate)."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Form koftas - Use wet hands so the mixture doesn&#39;t stick. Portion the mixture into 10 - 12 (70g / 1/3 cup each), and shape into a 10cm / 4&quot; cylinder. Thread onto skewers then slightly flatten to 1.75cm / 2/3&quot; thick. (Note 3)"
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "instruction": "Cook - Heat olive oil over medium high heat in a large non-stick pan. Cook half the koftas for 2 minutes on each side until golden, or until the internal temperature reaches 50°C/122°F."
    },
    {
      "order": 6,
      "instruction": "Rest - Remove onto a plate and cook the remaining koftas. (Internal temperature of cooked koftas will rise to 55°C/131°F)."
    },
    {
      "order": 7,
      "instruction": "Serve with Minted Yogurt and Jewelled rice pilaf for a stunning platter of food!"
    },
    {
      "order": 8,
      "instruction": "Blitz all ingredients in a tall jug just large enough to fit a stick blender. Keep refrigerated until required."
    }
  ]
}